      <article class="prose" style="padding:2rem 0;">
        <h1>About</h1>

        <p>
          I’m <strong>Carson Evans</strong>, a senior at the University of Massachusetts Boston
          pursuing a <strong>B.S. in Information Technology</strong> (Business Intelligence track).
          I run a small homelab (UniFi UCG Max, VLANs, Hyper-V, Docker on Windows &amp; Linux)
          and I care about pragmatic security and reliable ops.
        </p>

        <p>
          Lately I’ve been leveling up networking and cloud fundamentals and building
          simple, durable infrastructure that’s easy to maintain.
        </p>

        <h2>Interests</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Layer-3 / Layer-2 networking (routing, VLAN segmentation, remote access)</li>
          <li>AWS, CI/CD, and observability</li>
          <li>Automating the boring stuff (PowerShell, Python)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
